content.description: A relatively short, crimpy face.  The crux comes early and is short lived, but stands as a good intro to thin gorge crimping.  The top is easier, yet still interesting.
content.location: Far right hand side of the wall.

content.description: Crux comes right off the ground past the first bolt with fun roof finish.
content.location: In between Herniated Bone and Ace Cashier.

content.description: Face climb to the right of Behold. Looks like the crux is before and after 2nd bolt. Runout (but easy) after 3rd bolt (~20 feet)
content.protection: 4 bolts, shares anchor with Chicken Belly
content.location: 5 feet to the right of Behold

content.description:
Is it just me, or are ORG slab routes always hard for the grade?

A very sustained pitch with good variety that is slightly marred by a little bit of decomposing rock near the top.

Steep moves getting to the 1st bolt (10c) followed by a couple of hard moves pulling onto the slab (10c), easing off a bit then cruxing getting to the 4th bolt.  Some easier climbing on the edge of slab gets you to an interesting undercling/roof move which does not seem correctly bolted as a fall here could swing you into the slab.  A couple of steep, fun moves involving a crack, decomposing rock for the left foot and bomber stone on the right finish off the climbing.
content.protection: 8 bolts.  Might want a stick clip for the first.  Also might want to put a short draw on the 6th and make sure the belayer is paying attention at this point.
content.location: The leftmost route on the right sector of WOW, starting behind the northernmost trestle support.

content.description: Start off with an awkward move to the first bolt, rock quality seriously decreases between the 3rd to 5th bolts.
content.location: Left of Herniated Bone, past some broken stone

content.description: short warm up / senior route. ledge strike potential in the corner if you stray left during the first 3 bolts. crux is at the 6th bolt.
content.location: leftmost route on the wall.   can top rope lower section  of 10d from the anchors

content.description: It's a vertical dihedral.  Crux is right below the dihedral part of the climb where on the left hand side there is a triangular block that is tilted (between the 3rd and 4th bolt).
content.protection: 6 bolts.  Shares anchors with Mini me (5.11d).
content.location: Warm out wall in upper gorge.  Lower down off the anchors.
